column5: It was quite nice on Saturday so I stayed close and decided to fish Cowan.  I actually drove past the makeshift parking lot on the ice past the derby.  I drilled three holes and had luck with one of the holes.  This time the pike hit my jig while jigging.  One eater and a small one but both back into the lake.  It was good just to get a bite as I had been skunked for a while now.        By the way, does anybody know where the dawg is.
those are videos splash.........give em a clickin to see the fishies
You should get a tripod Holdy..... that way you can fight your fish and keep spike in check Nice couple of gators Thanks for sharing Leechman
Great report, I think you should teach Spike how to get the fish out of the hole for you, then you'll solve him getting in the way and he'll be happy  Joey
